CAPA_import( " ${CAPA_Tools}Problem " );   
TEXT(CAPA_EV (<<'END_OF_TEXT'));
Coals vary a lot in their energy content.  The energy released by the burning of coal is typically between 23 and 33 million \{ $J_u \} per \{ $kg_u \} of coal.  The power plant above uses coal that delivers \{  spf( $HC    , "%0.1f" ) \} million \{ $J_u \} per \{ $kg_u \} to make heat, some of which is converted in electrical energy, and some of which is dissipated as waste heat into the environment.  How many \{ $kg_u \} of coal are required to operate the power plant for 30 days?
END_OF_TEXT

## 
CAPA_hint( "The total average power (electrical + heat) from problem 7 times the number of seconds in 30 days gives you the average total energy.  Since you know the energy per kilogram of coal  you can calculate the number of kilograms.");   
## 

TEXT("$BR$BR",ans_rule(30),"$BR");
ANS( CAPA_ans( $Ad   , 'format' => "%0.2e" , 'sig' => '3 PLUS 13', 'reltol' => 1   ,  'wgt' => $prob_val    ,  'tries' => $prob_try    ,  'unit' => 'kg'    ) ); 
